- LLM changes
    - Use LangChain to do LLM based calls.
    - Give user name, conversation name, total time, remaining time (if interview is timed), extra details, job description text, today's date, and time, etc. in the prompt
    - The questions should have a flow:
        - If it is the beginning, then questions can be general
        - Towards the middle, the questions can be targeted
    - LLM should take a call to check the breadth as well as depth of understanding in the given timeframe
    - LLM should always focus on the job description and ask questions accordingly
    - LLM should have a memory of transcripts of all the queries and responses till now
    - LLM should have a very human like discussion
    - LLM should know if the interview is audio mode, video mode or text mode.
      In text mode, the input text is typed by the user (or recorded and then transcribed by STT model) and the output text is shown as text only.
      In audio mode, the input is received as an audio and then transcribed by STT model, then the output from LLM is converted to audio by TTS model and given to user along with the transcription.
      In video mode, the audio is same as audio mode, only a separate video feed is shown to the user, which is not given to the LLM at all.

